  "comment": "[gof-patterns] Implements a 5-tier cache hierarchy routing system with L1 to L5 performance tiers and associated algorithms.",
  "detail": "# Cache Module Documentation\n\n## Module Purpose and Architecture\n\nThis module implements a 5-tier cache hierarchy for query routing in an AI coding assistant system. The architecture follows a progressive refinement model where queries attempt faster, more specific caches first before falling back to slower but more comprehensive methods:\n\n- **L1 (Memory Cache)**: <10ms latency - Exact query hash lookup returning pre-rendered ContextNodes\n- **L2 (Workflow Cache)**: <50ms latency - Pre-compiled WASM tools via Extism\n- **L3 (Graph Traversal)**: <200ms latency - CozoDB Datalog queries\n- **L4 (Semantic Search)**: <500ms latency - KNN similarity search via embeddings\n- **L5 (LLM Fallback)**: >1s latency - External HTTP MCP call for complex reasoning\n\nThe system prioritizes query performance by caching results at multiple levels of abstraction, from exact matches to semantic approximations.\n\n## Key Abstractions and Relationships\n\n### Core Types\n\n**`CacheTier`** - Enum defining the five cache tiers with priority ordering (lower tier numbers = faster access). This serves as the primary abstraction for routing decisions.\n\n**`RoutingResult`** - Composite result struct containing:\n- `nodes`: Pre-rendered ContextNodes from database\n- `tool_result`: Binary tool execution output from WASM modules\n- `llm_response`: Text responses from external LLM services\n- `tier_used`: Which cache tier was successfully queried\n- `latency_ms`: Performance metric for routing optimization\n\n**`L1Cache`** - In-memory hash map cache with custom memory management. Unlike standard containers, it provides:\n- Ownership tracking via `dupeRoutingResult()` that deep-copies all heap allocations\n- Explicit deallocation via `freeRoutingResult()` that recursively frees nested data structures\n- Safe iteration and cleanup through proper iterator handling\n\n### Inter-Module Dependencies\n\nThe module integrates with four key subsystems:\n- **db_mod**: Provides ContextNode, Library, and hydration pipeline abstractions\n- **wasm_mod**: WASM tool execution via Extism runtime\n- **schema.zig**: Database schema definitions for query structures\n- **hashutil**: Query hashing utilities for consistent cache keys\n\n## Public API and Usage Patterns\n\n### Initialization Pattern\n```zig\nconst allocator = std.heap.ArenaAllocator.init(std.heap.page_allocator);\ndefer allocator.deinit();\n\nvar l1_cache = L1Cache.init(allocator.allocator());\ndefer l1_cache.deinit();\n```\n\n### Query Flow\n1. Compute query hash using `hashutil` utilities\n2. Attempt L1 cache lookup via `.get(query_hash)`\n3. On miss, cascade through L2-L5 tiers (external modules)\n4. Store result with `.put(query_hash, result)` for future queries\n5. Use `RoutingResult.tier_used` to optimize future routing decisions\n\n### Memory Safety Guarantees\nThe module implements strict ownership semantics:\n- All heap allocations are tracked in the cache structure\n- `dupeRoutingResult()` performs deep copies of all nested data\n- `freeRoutingResult()` recursively deallocates LOD arrays, strings, and nodes\n- Iterator-based cleanup ensures no memory leaks during deinitialization\n\n## Important Implementation Details\n\n### Nested Data Structure Handling\nContextNode contains Level-of-Detail (LOD) arrays that require special attention:\n```zig\nfor (result.nodes) |n| {\n    for (n.lod) |l| allocator.free(l);  // Free each LOD string\n}\nallocator.free(result.nodes);         // Free nodes array\n```\n\n### String Hash Map Configuration\nL1Cache uses `std.StringHashMap` with default settings optimized for:\n- O(1) average lookup time\n- Automatic collision handling\n- Memory-efficient key storage via owned keys\n\n### Latency Tracking\nThe `latency_ms` field enables adaptive routing by recording actual query times, allowing the system to learn which tiers perform best under different workloads.\n\n## Design Patterns\n\n1. **Tiered Fallback**: Progressive refinement from exact matches to semantic approximations\n2. **Cache-Aside**: External modules populate cache on miss rather than pre-warming\n3. **Custom Allocator Wrappers**: Encapsulates deep-copy semantics for complex nested structures\n4. **Dependency Injection**: Module dependencies injected via `@import` chains at compile time\n5. **Iterator-Based Cleanup**: Ensures safe, complete resource deallocation even with partial state",
